From cd3b268cd2f29b6033a3a5af207165fe68d0cbd7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cristian Ciocaltea <cristian.ciocaltea@collabora.com>
Date: Mon, 10 Nov 2025 11:31:27 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 082/114] [WIP-CRC] drm/rockchip: vop2: Add support for CRC
 generation

Implement CRC computation control and reporting through the DRM CRC
debugfs API.

Note the CRTC source is only supported by RK3576. Moreover, the frame
CRCs are *not* calculated at the final blending stage in VOP2 blending
pipeline, i.e. it happens before applying the background color, hence it
has limited usage in IGT testing.

Luckily, frame CRC generation can be done at DisplayPort AUX channel
level, hence provide support for DP and eDP CRC sources.

Signed-off-by: Cristian Ciocaltea <cristian.ciocaltea@collabora.com>
